%N A037585 Base 6 digits are, in order, the first n terms of the periodic sequence with initial period 3,1.
%H A037585 Zhuorui He, <a href="/A037585/b037585.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A037585 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (6,1,-6).
%F A037585 G.f.: x*(3+x) / ( (x-1)*(6*x-1)*(1+x) ). - _R. J. Mathar_, Apr 26 2015
%F A037585 a(n) = floor(19*6^n/35). - _Christian Krause_, Jun 07 2026
%t A037585 Table[FromDigits[PadRight[{},n,{3,1}],6],{n,20}] (* _Harvey P. Dale_, Jul 06 2025 *)
